WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:18.393 --> 00:00:20.353 position:50% align:center
[OBI] So this is our pic
for the nude calendar.

00:00:20.437 --> 00:00:22.522 position:50% align:center
Look at that
provocative expression.

00:00:22.605 --> 00:00:24.232 position:50% align:center
Way to go, Shinra!

00:00:24.315 --> 00:00:26.026 position:50% align:center
It wasn't deliberate, sir.

00:00:26.109 --> 00:00:30.030 position:50% align:center
I was just nervous about
taking my picture naked.

00:00:30.113 --> 00:00:31.823 position:50% align:center
[OBI]
Well, back to business.

00:00:31.906 --> 00:00:35.285 position:50% align:center
You're gonna get your sit-down
with Captain Hague of the 4th.

00:00:35.368 --> 00:00:37.162 position:50% align:center
If you're right
about what you saw,

00:00:37.245 --> 00:00:39.456 position:50% align:center
he may be able to help
you understand Adolla

00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:42.334 position:50% align:center
or find out the identity
of the Evangelist.

00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:43.918 position:50% align:center
He agreed to meet?

00:00:44.002 --> 00:00:45.170 position:50% align:center
[OBI]
Tomorrow.

00:00:45.253 --> 00:00:46.963 position:50% align:center
It probably would've been
harder to arrange,

00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:49.758 position:50% align:center
but the captain's granddaughter,
Lieutenant Asako,

00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:52.135 position:50% align:center
helped make it happen for you.

00:00:52.218 --> 00:00:55.513 position:50% align:center
She plans to accompany
you, by the way.

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.474 position:50% align:center
Are you familiar with the 4th?

00:00:57.557 --> 00:00:59.392 position:50% align:center
I know a few of
the people there.

00:00:59.476 --> 00:01:01.436 position:50% align:center
I was trained at
the 4th's Academy.

00:01:01.519 --> 00:01:03.855 position:50% align:center
It is the only one in
the Force after all.

00:01:03.938 --> 00:01:06.900 position:50% align:center
By the way, why does
the 4th handle training?

00:01:06.983 --> 00:01:09.277 position:50% align:center
[OBI] The Fire Defense
Agency commands the 4th

00:01:09.361 --> 00:01:11.279 position:50% align:center
and regular firefighters.

00:01:11.363 --> 00:01:13.323 position:50% align:center
It's in charge of
the Academy, too,

00:01:13.406 --> 00:01:15.950 position:50% align:center
and it uses the 4th
to manage it.

00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:17.994 position:50% align:center
So you say that you
saw Captain Hague

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:20.205 position:50% align:center
while you were having
an Adolla Link.

00:01:20.288 --> 00:01:21.998 position:50% align:center
It could be that
he agreed to see you

00:01:22.082 --> 00:01:24.918 position:50% align:center
because he's interested
in your Adolla Burst.

00:01:25.001 --> 00:01:26.878 position:50% align:center
Whatever his motives may be,

00:01:26.961 --> 00:01:29.839 position:50% align:center
this meeting should
be in our favor.

00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:32.050 position:50% align:center
Best of luck, Shinra.

00:01:34.969 --> 00:01:38.223 position:50% align:center
The boy with the
flame of salvation.

00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:14.778 position:50% align:center
Sure takes me back.

00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:18.573 position:50% align:center
[whistle blowing]

00:03:18.656 --> 00:03:19.699 position:50% align:center
Please excuse us.

00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:21.659 position:50% align:center
We hate to interrupt
your training.

00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:22.452 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:22.535 --> 00:03:24.120 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
Instructor Pan!

00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:27.916 position:50% align:center
It's been a while, Kusakabe.

00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:30.794 position:50% align:center
Forgive me. I should call
you Lieutenant Pan now.

00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:32.837 position:50% align:center
I thought they flushed
you down to the 8th--

00:03:32.921 --> 00:03:35.340 position:50% align:center
the cesspool where the
Force sends all its crap.

00:03:35.423 --> 00:03:36.383 position:50% align:center
A roach.

00:03:36.466 --> 00:03:37.509 position:50% align:center
They'd love to flush
you somewhere,

00:03:37.592 --> 00:03:39.219 position:50% align:center
but you'd just crawl
back up the pipes.

00:03:39.302 --> 00:03:40.428 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:03:40.512 --> 00:03:42.472 position:50% align:center
You watch your damn
mouth, mother-killer.

00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.143 position:50% align:center
I guess Company 4
doesn't teach this,

00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:48.812 position:50% align:center
but if you grab
someone carelessly,

00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:50.730 position:50% align:center
ya get joint-locked and thrown.

00:03:50.814 --> 00:03:52.565 position:50% align:center
It's just common
sense at the 8th.

00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:55.068 position:50% align:center
[4TH CREWMEN shouting]

00:03:55.151 --> 00:03:57.737 position:50% align:center
Just be glad that I didn't
break the wuss's arm.

00:03:57.821 --> 00:04:01.199 position:50% align:center
Calm it down, guys.
Karin's the one who started it.

00:04:01.282 --> 00:04:02.242 position:50% align:center
[KARIN growls]

00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:04.411 position:50% align:center
Kusakabe, you haven't
changed a bit.

00:04:04.494 --> 00:04:05.495 position:50% align:center
Ogun!

00:04:05.578 --> 00:04:07.247 position:50% align:center
You caught me off
guard, that's all.

00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:09.165 position:50% align:center
That sounds like
something you'd say.

00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:15.255 position:50% align:center
[whistle blowing]

00:04:17.590 --> 00:04:19.092 position:50% align:center
Sorry, sir?

00:04:19.175 --> 00:04:20.552 position:50% align:center
Please use your words.

00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:23.221 position:50% align:center
It's really hard to guess
what you mean from context.

00:04:23.304 --> 00:04:25.974 position:50% align:center
That's the Instructor
Pan I remember.

00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:30.145 position:50% align:center
You actually know quite
a few people here, don't you?

00:04:30.228 --> 00:04:33.273 position:50% align:center
This is my buddy Ogun.
He was at the top of our class.

00:04:33.356 --> 00:04:35.066 position:50% align:center
Shinra here didn't
have any friends,

00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:38.028 position:50% align:center
so Arthur and I decided
to let him run with us.

00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:40.155 position:50% align:center
You know that Arthur and
I aren't friends, right?

00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.740 position:50% align:center
'Course you aren't.

00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:43.616 position:50% align:center
Anyway, it looks like
you're doin' well.

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:44.951 position:50% align:center
Same goes for you.

00:04:45.035 --> 00:04:50.290 position:50% align:center
[whistle blowing]

00:04:50.373 --> 00:04:51.916 position:50% align:center
Lieutenant Pan said
he can take a minute

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.418 position:50% align:center
to show us to the captain.

00:04:53.501 --> 00:04:55.128 position:50% align:center
I'd appreciate that, sir.

00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.672 position:50% align:center
You can actually
understand him?

00:04:57.756 --> 00:05:01.843 position:50% align:center
[whistle blowing]

00:05:01.926 --> 00:05:03.595 position:50% align:center
So tell me, Lieutenant Asako,

00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:06.556 position:50% align:center
what business do you and the
8th have with Captain Hague?

00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:08.099 position:50% align:center
[ASAKO]
I wanted to ask my grandfather

00:05:08.183 --> 00:05:10.101 position:50% align:center
about the scar on his face.

00:05:10.185 --> 00:05:12.395 position:50% align:center
And about why he changed
after getting it.

00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:15.732 position:50% align:center
The captain's a great man
and a great leader.

00:05:15.815 --> 00:05:17.692 position:50% align:center
He was the first ever
regular firefighter

00:05:17.776 --> 00:05:21.071 position:50% align:center
to be promoted into the
ranks of the Fire Force.

00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:25.200 position:50% align:center
He's earned the full respect
of all of us here at the 4th.

00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:28.328 position:50% align:center
That still holds true, even now.

00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:31.915 position:50% align:center
Here's his office. He wants
to see you alone, Kusakabe.

00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:33.416 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
Do you know why?

00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:34.876 position:50% align:center
[ASAKO] I told him that
you wanted to talk

00:05:34.959 --> 00:05:37.253 position:50% align:center
about Adolla Bursts,
and since that isn't a subject,

00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:38.672 position:50% align:center
I know much about,

00:05:38.755 --> 00:05:41.007 position:50% align:center
I think its best if I stay
out of the way for now.

00:05:41.091 --> 00:05:43.009 position:50% align:center
I'll talk to him later.

00:05:43.093 --> 00:05:45.929 position:50% align:center
Well, in that case, here goes.

00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:48.973 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
Excuse me, sir.

00:05:53.478 --> 00:05:55.730 position:50% align:center
Captain Hague, thanks
for meeting me, sir.

00:05:55.814 --> 00:05:59.109 position:50% align:center
Name's Shinra Kusakabe.
I'm a second-class Fire Soldier.

00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:01.361 position:50% align:center
Here from Company 8.

00:06:01.444 --> 00:06:03.446 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
I've been expecting you.

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:08.034 position:50% align:center
Let's get right to the point.
I'd like to see your flames.

00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:12.539 position:50% align:center
Actually, I'd like
to feel their heat.

00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:14.499 position:50% align:center
Oh, that didn't
startle you, did it?

00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:15.834 position:50% align:center
Of course it did, forgive me.

00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:17.460 position:50% align:center
I should've spoken
more carefully.

00:06:17.544 --> 00:06:19.629 position:50% align:center
The last thing I want is
to make you uncomfortable,

00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:22.424 position:50% align:center
so why don't I try that again?

00:06:22.507 --> 00:06:25.427 position:50% align:center
I want you to burn me
without holding back.

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:26.594 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
Whoa.

00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:28.013 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
Go on.

00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:29.514 position:50% align:center
Just do it. Just do it!
Do it! Do it!

00:06:29.597 --> 00:06:30.724 position:50% align:center
You want me to burn you?

00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:34.269 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE] Yes! Burn me
with all your strength!

00:06:34.352 --> 00:06:35.437 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR]
What's wrong?

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:37.939 position:50% align:center
He's begging you to
burn him, so do it.

00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:38.940 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:39.024 --> 00:06:40.316 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR]
Burn him. Burn him.

00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:41.943 position:50% align:center
Burn him to death.

00:06:42.027 --> 00:06:45.864 position:50% align:center
I know your flames are
bursting to get out.

00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:47.615 position:50% align:center
Kill that horrible demon.

00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:49.951 position:50% align:center
Wipe it from the
face of the earth.

00:06:50.035 --> 00:06:51.286 position:50% align:center
No way.

00:06:51.369 --> 00:06:54.289 position:50% align:center
That demon was Mom,
and I would never hurt her.

00:06:54.372 --> 00:06:56.166 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR] Then what's
to become of the bloodlust

00:06:56.249 --> 00:06:58.877 position:50% align:center
you've been building up
for the last 12 years?

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:01.171 position:50% align:center
It won't just
disappear, ya know.

00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:02.297 position:50% align:center
Ugly devil.

00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:03.882 position:50% align:center
--It's the mother-killer.
--So creepy.

00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:05.300 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR]
You held back.

00:07:05.383 --> 00:07:08.219 position:50% align:center
Let those little turds say
whatever they wanted.

00:07:08.303 --> 00:07:10.013 position:50% align:center
You told yourself
killing the demon

00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:11.639 position:50% align:center
would make it all worth it.

00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:13.808 position:50% align:center
Your rage would have
a place to go.

00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:15.977 position:50% align:center
You were wrong,
but if you want relief,

00:07:16.061 --> 00:07:18.438 position:50% align:center
then all you have to do
is start burning!

00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:20.190 position:50% align:center
Say to the world, "You're right.

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:22.525 position:50% align:center
I am every bit the
devil you said I was."

00:07:22.609 --> 00:07:24.402 position:50% align:center
Give up on the hero thing.

00:07:24.486 --> 00:07:27.447 position:50% align:center
This world was built on
a stinking bed of lies.

00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:30.408 position:50% align:center
Heroes aren't real.

00:07:30.492 --> 00:07:32.577 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR laughs]

00:07:32.660 --> 00:07:34.954 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR] He's the one
you really wanna burn, huh?

00:07:35.038 --> 00:07:37.165 position:50% align:center
I mean, he hid
everything from you.

00:07:37.248 --> 00:07:41.961 position:50% align:center
That wasn't his call
to make. This is on him.

00:07:42.045 --> 00:07:43.421 position:50% align:center
So burn.

00:07:43.505 --> 00:07:46.549 position:50% align:center
Release your flames and
you'll feel much better.

00:07:46.633 --> 00:07:52.430 position:50% align:center
Go ahead. Be free!
Let go of all of that anger.

00:07:52.514 --> 00:07:54.182 position:50% align:center
Sister?

00:07:54.265 --> 00:07:57.727 position:50% align:center
Burn it all. Drown your
pain in a sea of fire.

00:07:57.811 --> 00:08:00.730 position:50% align:center
Hold on, there's no
way you're the Sister.

00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:03.149 position:50% align:center
Tell me who you are really.

00:08:04.192 --> 00:08:08.238 position:50% align:center
That must've been an
Adolla Link, right?

00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.864 position:50% align:center
I wonder if it might
have been triggered

00:08:09.948 --> 00:08:11.700 position:50% align:center
by your proximity to me.

00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:15.537 position:50% align:center
And you saw a mysterious woman
who resembled someone you know?

00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:18.957 position:50% align:center
I just wish I could meet
this angel for myself.

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.084 position:50% align:center
I want you to burn
me even more now.

00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:22.377 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA gasps]

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:23.962 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
I wanted to ask.

00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:26.256 position:50% align:center
Have you ever had
an Adolla Link?

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:28.842 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE] If that's what you
want to call it, then yes.

00:08:28.925 --> 00:08:31.928 position:50% align:center
It was a magnificent experience.

00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:33.471 position:50% align:center
Captain Burns had one, too.

00:08:33.555 --> 00:08:35.807 position:50% align:center
He said he paid for it
with his right eye.

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:37.100 position:50% align:center
What price did you pay?

00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:39.519 position:50% align:center
Does it have to do
with your scar?

00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:42.230 position:50% align:center
Until that day, I had spent
my life working hard

00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:45.567 position:50% align:center
and doing my damnedest to
protect all the people I could.

00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:51.197 position:50% align:center
But then, around two years ago,
my way of thinking was changed.

00:08:51.281 --> 00:08:53.408 position:50% align:center
The Great Fire was ravenous.

00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:57.454 position:50% align:center
It swallowed up the whole city,
taking countless lives.

00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:58.872 position:50% align:center
It forced me to recognize

00:08:58.955 --> 00:09:02.667 position:50% align:center
that I'd failed many more
people than I'd saved.

00:09:05.503 --> 00:09:07.505 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:07.589 --> 00:09:08.840 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
In that moment,

00:09:08.923 --> 00:09:11.801 position:50% align:center
I felt a hope that was
much like despair.

00:09:11.885 --> 00:09:14.346 position:50% align:center
A sense of liberation.

00:09:14.429 --> 00:09:17.474 position:50% align:center
It was like everything
had been saved.

00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:19.059 position:50% align:center
An "Adolla Link."

00:09:19.142 --> 00:09:21.770 position:50% align:center
Is that what such a
baptism is called?

00:09:21.853 --> 00:09:23.730 position:50% align:center
What I saw there was
not the sunlight

00:09:23.813 --> 00:09:26.858 position:50% align:center
I've been told to
revere by the Temple.

00:09:26.941 --> 00:09:30.987 position:50% align:center
It was the blessed light of God.

00:09:31.071 --> 00:09:32.322 position:50% align:center
I believe that divine realm

00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:35.700 position:50% align:center
to be the very
salvation of mankind.

00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:38.036 position:50% align:center
This claw mark is my stigmata.

00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:40.497 position:50% align:center
It's the truth
carved into my being.

00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:42.957 position:50% align:center
The scar that opened my eyes.

00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:44.709 position:50% align:center
Forgive me,
but I must ask again.

00:09:44.793 --> 00:09:47.921 position:50% align:center
Please, Kusakabe, set me
alight with your holy flames!

00:09:48.004 --> 00:09:50.256 position:50% align:center
Let me see that
divine realm again!

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:51.591 position:50% align:center
Hold on just a minute.

00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:53.468 position:50% align:center
Captain Hague, are you
seriously saying you think

00:09:53.551 --> 00:09:56.930 position:50% align:center
that unearthly hellscape
is actually holy?

00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:59.224 position:50% align:center
Whether that realm is
considered sacred or profane

00:09:59.307 --> 00:10:01.309 position:50% align:center
means nothing to me.

00:10:01.393 --> 00:10:03.895 position:50% align:center
The gods and devils mortals
imagine unto themselves

00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:06.815 position:50% align:center
are mere imitations of Adolla.

00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:09.943 position:50% align:center
Be it heaven or hell,
it was the truth.

00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:11.569 position:50% align:center
I only wish I could
share that truth

00:10:11.653 --> 00:10:14.030 position:50% align:center
so that all the world
could be enlightened!

00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:15.990 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA] I didn't feel
anything like salvation

00:10:16.074 --> 00:10:18.535 position:50% align:center
when I had my Adolla links.

00:10:18.618 --> 00:10:19.786 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
You hold an Adolla Burst,

00:10:19.869 --> 00:10:22.372 position:50% align:center
so it may well feel
mundane to you.

00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:26.001 position:50% align:center
However, I am but a human being.

00:10:27.335 --> 00:10:29.379 position:50% align:center
I'm as human as you are.

00:10:29.462 --> 00:10:31.339 position:50% align:center
[ASAKO screams]

00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:37.012 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
The mascots?

00:10:39.889 --> 00:10:42.809 position:50% align:center
Shinra Kusakabe. Prepare to die.

00:10:42.892 --> 00:10:44.853 position:50% align:center
Are you serious right now?

00:10:44.936 --> 00:10:46.146 position:50% align:center
You can't really be that upset

00:10:46.229 --> 00:10:48.148 position:50% align:center
just 'cause I flipped
you on your back.

00:10:48.231 --> 00:10:49.733 position:50% align:center
This is your chance.

00:10:49.816 --> 00:10:53.028 position:50% align:center
If that twerp wants a fight to
the death, then give him one.

00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.032 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
What's come over you three?

00:10:57.115 --> 00:10:58.324 position:50% align:center
[FIRST PILLAR]
Kill him.

00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:01.077 position:50% align:center
You finally have a target
for your rage, Shinra.

00:11:01.161 --> 00:11:03.413 position:50% align:center
So let it out. Burn him.

00:11:03.496 --> 00:11:05.373 position:50% align:center
Burn them all.

00:11:05.457 --> 00:11:07.625 position:50% align:center
I should burn everything.

00:11:07.709 --> 00:11:09.127 position:50% align:center
What did you just say?

00:11:09.210 --> 00:11:11.338 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's what
I'm talkin' about!

00:11:11.421 --> 00:11:13.548 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
I'll burn it all down!

00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:15.800 position:50% align:center
Do it.

00:11:15.884 --> 00:11:19.220 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
So this is your Adolla Burst.

00:11:19.304 --> 00:11:21.639 position:50% align:center
I love it. I love it!

00:11:21.723 --> 00:11:23.391 position:50% align:center
--[whistle blows]
--[ASAKO] Grandpa!

00:11:23.475 --> 00:11:25.435 position:50% align:center
Seems like our crewmen
have lost their minds.

00:11:25.518 --> 00:11:27.437 position:50% align:center
Kusakabe's acting strange, too.

00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:30.315 position:50% align:center
It's almost like the four
of them have been possessed.

00:11:30.398 --> 00:11:31.816 position:50% align:center
--[VOICE C] Mother-killer!
--[VOICE A] He's such a creep.

00:11:31.900 --> 00:11:33.401 position:50% align:center
--[VOICE D] Devil!
--[VOICE B] You're a devil!

00:11:33.485 --> 00:11:36.613 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA] They said all that crap
even though they knew nothing.

00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:38.990 position:50% align:center
Or maybe I'm the one
who knew nothing.

00:11:39.074 --> 00:11:42.911 position:50% align:center
Like it matters.
I've had enough.

00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:46.206 position:50% align:center
All of you can drop dead.

00:11:46.289 --> 00:11:48.708 position:50% align:center
You need to start
behaving yourselves.

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.972 position:50% align:center
I just wanted to use
some Company 4 soldiers

00:12:03.056 --> 00:12:04.432 position:50% align:center
to get under Shinra's skin,

00:12:04.516 --> 00:12:06.810 position:50% align:center
but it looks like the First
Pillar's beaten me to it.

00:12:06.893 --> 00:12:08.311 position:50% align:center
Wait, the First Pillar?

00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:10.772 position:50% align:center
Hey, Haumea, did you actually
just say the First Pillar?

00:12:10.855 --> 00:12:12.565 position:50% align:center
"Under his skin"?
Well, how do you mean?

00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:14.776 position:50% align:center
Is she using an Adolla Link
to contact him or what?

00:12:14.859 --> 00:12:15.860 position:50% align:center
You've gotta tell me!

00:12:15.944 --> 00:12:17.153 position:50% align:center
[HAUMEA]
Shut up, Charon!

00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:18.363 position:50% align:center
If you're gonna
be this annoying,

00:12:18.446 --> 00:12:19.781 position:50% align:center
you may as well just die!

00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:20.824 position:50% align:center
[CHARON]
Come on, just tell me

00:12:20.907 --> 00:12:21.950 position:50% align:center
if she came through
an Adolla Link!

00:12:22.033 --> 00:12:23.952 position:50% align:center
[HAUMEA]
Yes! Of course it was, dumbass!

00:12:24.035 --> 00:12:24.994 position:50% align:center
Are you stupid?

00:12:25.078 --> 00:12:26.996 position:50% align:center
We know where the
First Pillar is.

00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:28.248 position:50% align:center
And since we know she's there,

00:12:28.331 --> 00:12:30.542 position:50% align:center
she obviously didn't
come here in person.

00:12:30.625 --> 00:12:32.919 position:50% align:center
She's using an Adolla
Link to possess Shinra.

00:12:33.003 --> 00:12:35.005 position:50% align:center
His hate and anger
caught her attention,

00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.798 position:50% align:center
so she mixed it with her own.

00:12:36.881 --> 00:12:39.634 position:50% align:center
Now she's got him in perfect
sync with her craziness.

00:12:39.718 --> 00:12:42.053 position:50% align:center
Against them, we have that
old elite fireman captain

00:12:42.137 --> 00:12:44.931 position:50% align:center
and his buff-slinging
lieutenant.

00:12:45.015 --> 00:12:46.516 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:12:49.978 --> 00:12:54.315 position:50% align:center
Know what? I'd like to
take this out of my office.

00:12:54.399 --> 00:12:57.068 position:50% align:center
I'd like to avoid burning
down my fire station.

00:12:57.152 --> 00:12:58.570 position:50% align:center
Type One Fire Axes!

00:12:58.653 --> 00:13:00.196 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:13:02.699 --> 00:13:05.785 position:50% align:center
It feels like I'm up against
a beast in human clothing.

00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:08.371 position:50% align:center
There's no need
to hold back anymore.

00:13:08.455 --> 00:13:11.791 position:50% align:center
Let's kill them.
Whoever gets in our way.

00:13:11.875 --> 00:13:13.501 position:50% align:center
[SHINRA]
Who is this girl?

00:13:13.585 --> 00:13:17.797 position:50% align:center
How can she feel so much
hatred? It's overpowering.

00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:21.676 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE yells]

00:13:21.760 --> 00:13:23.428 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
It's hot! Ahh!

00:13:23.511 --> 00:13:25.930 position:50% align:center
Adolla! Adolla!

00:13:26.014 --> 00:13:27.182 position:50% align:center
[PAN]
What are you doing, Captain?

00:13:27.265 --> 00:13:28.725 position:50% align:center
You should've been
able to avoid that!

00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:30.226 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:33.063 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
It's good. So very good.

00:13:33.146 --> 00:13:34.564 position:50% align:center
Even knowing that it'll kill me

00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:37.359 position:50% align:center
if I bask in its warmth
for too long...

00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:39.569 position:50% align:center
...I want more. Yes, I do.

00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:40.862 position:50% align:center
Something's wrong with him.

00:13:40.945 --> 00:13:43.573 position:50% align:center
Pull it together, sir!
He really could kill you!

00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:44.908 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
Kill me?

00:13:44.991 --> 00:13:48.495 position:50% align:center
No, I need to stick around
for the sake of the 4th.

00:13:48.578 --> 00:13:50.121 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:51.831 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE] Ah, that's incredible
in its own right!

00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:53.041 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:13:53.124 --> 00:13:54.542 position:50% align:center
Even with me boosting
his heat resistance,

00:13:54.626 --> 00:13:56.586 position:50% align:center
the captain won't
last much longer.

00:13:56.670 --> 00:13:59.089 position:50% align:center
[PAN]
Just dodge.

00:13:59.172 --> 00:14:01.174 position:50% align:center
I know those flame spears.

00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:04.177 position:50% align:center
This guy thinks he can visit my
company and trash the place.

00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:06.763 position:50% align:center
I can't even take my eyes
off him for a minute.

00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:08.682 position:50% align:center
You made it just in time, Ogun!

00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:10.433 position:50% align:center
And... Arthur?

00:14:10.517 --> 00:14:12.644 position:50% align:center
My captain thought the
electricity user we fought

00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:15.146 position:50% align:center
in the Nether might
try to come after Shinra.

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:18.775 position:50% align:center
So he asked me to follow Shinra
here and play bodyguard.

00:14:22.362 --> 00:14:25.115 position:50% align:center
Something's not right.
Is that really you, Shinra?

00:14:25.198 --> 00:14:26.449 position:50% align:center
What happened?

00:14:26.533 --> 00:14:28.910 position:50% align:center
Is that woman from the
Nether making you do this?

00:14:28.993 --> 00:14:33.164 position:50% align:center
No, wait. I'm sensing yet
another presence inside you.

00:14:33.248 --> 00:14:35.709 position:50% align:center
Burn you. Burn you.

00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:39.045 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
You look hideous. As usual.

00:14:39.129 --> 00:14:40.505 position:50% align:center
Time for a devil hunt.

00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:41.881 position:50% align:center
Slow down.

00:14:41.965 --> 00:14:44.175 position:50% align:center
Step one is to try 'n bring
him back to his senses.

00:14:44.259 --> 00:14:46.386 position:50% align:center
That's easy to say,
but where do we start?

00:14:46.469 --> 00:14:48.805 position:50% align:center
If it was an Adolla Link
that caused Kusakabe

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:50.515 position:50% align:center
to start acting this way,

00:14:50.598 --> 00:14:52.559 position:50% align:center
then perhaps we should
break that link.

00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:55.020 position:50% align:center
Hang back, sir, you're like
a moth to his flames.

00:14:55.103 --> 00:14:57.522 position:50% align:center
You two stop him before
he can cause more damage.

00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:58.440 position:50% align:center
I'll back you up!

00:14:58.523 --> 00:15:00.066 position:50% align:center
He's coming.

00:15:01.776 --> 00:15:02.819 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:06.448 position:50% align:center
He's that fast?
No way. I couldn't see--

00:15:06.531 --> 00:15:07.574 position:50% align:center
[OGUN coughing]

00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:09.242 position:50% align:center
I used my
muscle-enhancing whistle

00:15:09.325 --> 00:15:10.869 position:50% align:center
to increase your durability.

00:15:10.952 --> 00:15:12.871 position:50% align:center
Yeah, well, it hurt
like hell anyway.

00:15:12.954 --> 00:15:15.206 position:50% align:center
Hey, now, no fair.

00:15:15.290 --> 00:15:17.834 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR] So that's what it's
like to get hit by the Rapid.

00:15:17.917 --> 00:15:20.503 position:50% align:center
I saw it coming, but my
body couldn't keep up.

00:15:20.587 --> 00:15:23.298 position:50% align:center
[PAN] Just attack him.
I'll keep you buffed and healed.

00:15:23.381 --> 00:15:25.175 position:50% align:center
[OGUN] 'Kay. Let's
fight him as a party.

00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:27.802 position:50% align:center
I'll tank. You DPS.

00:15:27.886 --> 00:15:31.765 position:50% align:center
[PAN] I, Pan the Bard, shall
inspire you with my magic flute.

00:15:31.848 --> 00:15:34.976 position:50% align:center
[OGUN] I, Ogun the Warrior,
will avenge my village!

00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:37.020 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE]
I am the Shield of Masochism,

00:15:37.103 --> 00:15:39.481 position:50% align:center
forged by the dwarves!

00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:41.107 position:50% align:center
[ASAKO]
What is this?

00:15:41.191 --> 00:15:42.442 position:50% align:center
[OGUN]
Let's go, Knight King!

00:15:42.525 --> 00:15:45.570 position:50% align:center
I'll slay this demon myself.

00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:47.280 position:50% align:center
[PAN]
Wait, what was that?

00:15:47.364 --> 00:15:48.782 position:50% align:center
You're acting weird.

00:15:48.865 --> 00:15:51.242 position:50% align:center
Is he being controlled
like Karin and the others?

00:15:51.326 --> 00:15:54.621 position:50% align:center
He's fine. In fact,
this is what we want.

00:15:54.704 --> 00:15:56.539 position:50% align:center
Is he pretending to
be a knight again?

00:15:56.623 --> 00:15:58.833 position:50% align:center
[OGUN] Yeah. He looks
mad dumb right now.

00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:01.086 position:50% align:center
I mean, I've never seen him
look quite this dumb before.

00:16:01.169 --> 00:16:02.462 position:50% align:center
He must be goin' pretty deep.

00:16:02.545 --> 00:16:04.506 position:50% align:center
I wonder what could've
triggered this.

00:16:08.551 --> 00:16:10.512 position:50% align:center
Take me to Adolla!

00:16:10.595 --> 00:16:13.306 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
Force Shield!

00:16:13.390 --> 00:16:14.641 position:50% align:center
Shield Bash!

00:16:14.724 --> 00:16:15.350 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:16:15.433 --> 00:16:16.601 position:50% align:center
Damn it, Arthur!

00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:18.103 position:50% align:center
What do you think you're
doing with my captain?

00:16:18.186 --> 00:16:20.271 position:50% align:center
Don't worry.
The shield held true.

00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:23.525 position:50% align:center
I've never been used
like this before.

00:16:23.608 --> 00:16:26.194 position:50% align:center
[PAN]
Please stop enjoying that, sir!

00:16:26.277 --> 00:16:27.696 position:50% align:center
[HAGUE chuckles]

00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:35.120 position:50% align:center
Tell me, Shinra, what happened
to becoming a hero?

00:16:35.203 --> 00:16:40.375 position:50% align:center
I burned that worthless idea
into ashes and set myself free.

00:16:40.458 --> 00:16:42.127 position:50% align:center
Well, that doesn't
sound like you.

00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:45.422 position:50% align:center
Makes me wonder if it's
you who's talking.

00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:48.049 position:50% align:center
What am I to glean from
that smile, Shinra?

00:16:48.133 --> 00:16:51.177 position:50% align:center
Are you simply excited to
reveal your true nature?

00:16:51.261 --> 00:16:54.806 position:50% align:center
Or is it a sign that you need
the Knight King's aid?

00:16:54.889 --> 00:16:56.391 position:50% align:center
I know just what you want.

00:16:56.474 --> 00:16:59.394 position:50% align:center
I know where Mommy is.
I know how you can find her.

00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:00.854 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
All right, Devil. Hear me well!

00:17:00.937 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
You're getting three chances.

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.066 position:50% align:center
The first three times you
assail me, I'll let you go.

00:17:05.150 --> 00:17:06.901 position:50% align:center
The fourth time, I'll slay you.

00:17:06.985 --> 00:17:09.404 position:50% align:center
So come to your senses before--

00:17:09.487 --> 00:17:11.239 position:50% align:center
Hey, are you even
listening to me?

00:17:11.322 --> 00:17:13.450 position:50% align:center
You only get four chances!

00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:19.205 position:50% align:center
That makes one.

00:17:19.289 --> 00:17:20.957 position:50% align:center
You've always become
a real powerhouse

00:17:21.041 --> 00:17:22.834 position:50% align:center
when you get into your roleplay.

00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:25.920 position:50% align:center
D'ya know why you're
the way that you are?

00:17:26.004 --> 00:17:27.380 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
It's how I was brought up.

00:17:27.464 --> 00:17:30.008 position:50% align:center
I was born and raised
a king of knights.

00:17:30.091 --> 00:17:32.302 position:50% align:center
[OGUN] Does that mean
you're a blueblood?

00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:35.597 position:50% align:center
Seriously, what kinda
household did you grow up in?

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:37.724 position:50% align:center
A blueblood? Uh.

00:17:37.807 --> 00:17:40.935 position:50% align:center
If royal blood
is blue, then yes.

00:17:41.019 --> 00:17:44.439 position:50% align:center
As for the household I
was raised in, well...

00:17:44.522 --> 00:17:45.815 position:50% align:center
[TV REPORTER A]
Though the fire was put out

00:17:45.899 --> 00:17:47.817 position:50% align:center
in the early hours of
yesterday morning,

00:17:47.901 --> 00:17:50.153 position:50% align:center
the restaurant in question
was already in debt

00:17:50.236 --> 00:17:51.488 position:50% align:center
on account of a high-profile...

00:17:51.571 --> 00:17:53.990 position:50% align:center
Looks like they're talking
about us on the news.

00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:55.867 position:50% align:center
What are we gonna do?

00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:58.161 position:50% align:center
Let your dad know that
dinner's ready, Arthur.

00:17:58.244 --> 00:17:59.913 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
Roger that.

00:17:59.996 --> 00:18:02.791 position:50% align:center
Hey, Dad, it's time
for our last supper.

00:18:04.959 --> 00:18:09.839 position:50% align:center
Mom says all our pinched
pennies went up in smoke. Hm?

00:18:09.923 --> 00:18:11.966 position:50% align:center
Is there somethin'
on your mind, Arthur?

00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:13.885 position:50% align:center
Why were you staring
into your hat?

00:18:13.968 --> 00:18:15.679 position:50% align:center
Can you see something inside?

00:18:15.762 --> 00:18:19.766 position:50% align:center
You always ask me the funniest
questions, ya know that?

00:18:19.849 --> 00:18:21.309 position:50% align:center
'Course you can.

00:18:21.393 --> 00:18:24.479 position:50% align:center
You can check out the whole
star-studded sky with this hat.

00:18:24.562 --> 00:18:27.065 position:50% align:center
It can show you anything.

00:18:27.148 --> 00:18:28.692 position:50% align:center
You liar, it's pitch-black.

00:18:28.775 --> 00:18:31.111 position:50% align:center
I can't see a thing
inside this hat.

00:18:31.194 --> 00:18:33.279 position:50% align:center
You sure about that?

00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:35.990 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:36.074 --> 00:18:37.325 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
I see a castle.

00:18:37.409 --> 00:18:38.743 position:50% align:center
It's your castle!

00:18:38.827 --> 00:18:39.869 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR'S FATHER]
A castle, huh?

00:18:39.953 --> 00:18:41.454 position:50% align:center
Ha! That's awesome!

00:18:41.538 --> 00:18:43.540 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR] You've got lots
of soldiers, too.

00:18:43.623 --> 00:18:46.209 position:50% align:center
Hey. What are you
two doing in here?

00:18:48.211 --> 00:18:52.173 position:50% align:center
Come on, Sir Arthur.
We have a royal ball to attend.

00:18:57.512 --> 00:18:59.389 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:16.281 position:50% align:center
King?

00:19:16.364 --> 00:19:20.785 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR] Ever since that day,
I've been the Knight King.

00:19:20.869 --> 00:19:23.121 position:50% align:center
It sounds like your
parents just took off.

00:19:23.204 --> 00:19:24.039 position:50% align:center
I think they abandoned--

00:19:24.122 --> 00:19:25.623 position:50% align:center
[whistle blows]

00:19:31.296 --> 00:19:32.630 position:50% align:center
You have one chance left.

00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:34.424 position:50% align:center
Will you forsake your
dream and perish?

00:19:34.507 --> 00:19:37.177 position:50% align:center
Why would I ever
wanna be a hero?

00:19:40.555 --> 00:19:42.766 position:50% align:center
I really will have to
cut him down soon,

00:19:42.849 --> 00:19:44.184 position:50% align:center
lest he should kill me.

00:19:44.267 --> 00:19:45.769 position:50% align:center
Heroes aren't just
cooler than knights,

00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:47.312 position:50% align:center
they're also way stronger.

00:19:47.395 --> 00:19:50.690 position:50% align:center
Heh. I can see why a fool
like you would think that.

00:19:50.774 --> 00:19:51.691 position:50% align:center
[OGUN]
You guys know we're trainin'

00:19:51.775 --> 00:19:53.401 position:50% align:center
to be Fire Soldiers, right?

00:19:53.485 --> 00:19:55.612 position:50% align:center
So, not knights or heroes.

00:19:55.695 --> 00:19:58.948 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR] I'll expose your true
nature one of these days, Devil.

00:19:59.032 --> 00:20:01.409 position:50% align:center
I have to be a hero, understand?

00:20:01.493 --> 00:20:03.453 position:50% align:center
I made my family a promise.

00:20:03.536 --> 00:20:05.205 position:50% align:center
You're serious.

00:20:05.288 --> 00:20:07.999 position:50% align:center
It seems we have one
thing in common.

00:20:08.083 --> 00:20:10.960 position:50% align:center
I used to respect you for
keeping your oath at least,

00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:12.962 position:50% align:center
but now you're
nothing but a devil!

00:20:13.046 --> 00:20:14.172 position:50% align:center
I don't care!

00:20:14.255 --> 00:20:15.715 position:50% align:center
If it helps me kill the
demon that got my mom,

00:20:15.799 --> 00:20:17.509 position:50% align:center
then of course I'll be a devil!

00:20:17.592 --> 00:20:19.719 position:50% align:center
Except that demon was
your mother, right?

00:20:19.803 --> 00:20:21.179 position:50% align:center
Right, good point.

00:20:21.262 --> 00:20:23.223 position:50% align:center
